# GitHub Linguist configuration.
#
# Nova is not yet in the upstream github/linguist database, so GitHub cannot
# render the literal label "Nova" — an unknown `linguist-language=Nova` is
# ignored, and there is NO per-repo way to define a brand-new language. The only
# real fix is the upstream contribution in linguist/ (adoption-gated, outside
# this repo). We deliberately do NOT mislabel `.nova` as another language (an
# earlier interim mapped it to Rust, which hid Nova entirely) — better honest
# than wrong.
*.nova linguist-language=Nova linguist-detectable=true

# Generated / vendored / non-source trees don't count toward the language stats.
nova/target/**        linguist-generated=true
nova/nova_modules/**  linguist-vendored=true
bench/**              linguist-vendored=true
*.lock                linguist-generated=true
